Class NamespaceRemover

@QAInfo(level=NORMAL,
        state=IN_DEVELOPMENT,
        author="te")
public class NamespaceRemover
extends ReplaceReader

A Java 1.5 compatible Reader which removes namespace declaration from XML. If you are looking for namespace agnostic XSLT transformations use the static methods supplied on the on the XSLT class, eg. XSLT.transform(java.net.URL, String, boolean).

The reader looks for the pattern "<.*>". For each match, all elements matching "xmlns:?[a-z]*=\".*\"" are removed. If "" is encountered, it is copied verbatim. if "" is encountered, it is copied verbatim.

This reader reads ahead, so the parent Reader is not guaranteed to be positioned at any deterministic position during processing.

The reader is not thread-safe.
